(4168, 250, '_accordion_section_0_accordion_color', 'field_5397901e00c44'),
(4169, 250, 'accordion_section_0_accordion_content', 'Ideally fencing should be built along the edge of the setback or buffer along the riparian zone. This allows the filtration services provided by the buffer to continue. However, if this is not possible, fences should be built along a setback, which will help to provide some protection from flooding during the spring and ice during the winter.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/farming/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Riparian-Fencing.png"><img class=" wp-image-274 aligncenter" src="http://localhost/farming/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Riparian-Fencing-300x130.png" alt="Riparian Fencing" width="659" height="285" /></a>\r\n\r\nOf course livestock will need access to water. Ideally an alternative water source can be used. Sometimes, however, watercourses provide the only feasible possibility for drinking water. By limiting the location of where livestock have access to the stream their negative impact on the watercourse will be lessened. By restricting access to only the waters edge, many negatives can be avoided.'),
