(329, 1, '2014-06-26 15:27:06', '2014-06-26 15:27:06', 'By raising the cutting height of the blades on your mower, it is possible to reduce the number of field fauna casualties. Raising the height by 10cm will have little impact on the nutritional quality of the hay (there is little nutritional value to the woody stalks), but will have a significant impact on the survival rate of different species, including the threatened wood turtle.\r\n\r\n<a name="_GoBack"></a> Furthermore, increasing the cutting height has also been linked to a decrease in damage to machinery, increased soil health (as soil structure is maintained), and reduced susceptibility to erosion.', 'Raising Cutting Height', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'raising-cutting-height', '', '', '2014-06-26 15:27:06', '2014-06-26 15:27:06', '', 317, 'http://localhost/farming/?page_id=329', 0, 'page', '', 0),
